  "prompt": "Is calibri with font size 9 good for resume?",
  "response": "Using Calibri with a font size of 9 for a resume is generally not recommended. While Calibri is a clean and modern font that is widely accepted for professional documents, a font size of 9 is quite small and can be difficult to read. Typically, font sizes between 10.5 to 12 points are recommended to ensure readability and that your resume looks polished and professional. The goal is to make sure your resume is easily legible to hiring managers, so it's better to prioritize clarity over fitting more content onto the page.",
